The paper deals with the problem of matching residents to hospitals, which is a well-studied problem in the field of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also proposes algorithms for computing popular and envy-free matchings, which are optimization problems that can be tackled using artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The paper involves the analysis of algorithms and the complexity of the problem, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves experiments on synthetic and real-world datasets, which can be considered as a study in machine learning and data analysis (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a practical alternative to stable matchings, which can be considered as a study in optimization and decision-making (cs.LG).
